issue.title: Fix: Query 관련 버그 수정
issue.body:
- 경로 변수는 Path로 받아야 하는데 query로 설정하여 Error 발생
`AssertionError: Cannot use Query for path param 'uid'`

- 나의 독서기록 조회 관련 쿼리 조회 결과를 객체로 그대로 남기는 문제를 해결
`row = (
        db.query(FairyTale, FairyTaleLog)
        .join(FairyTaleLog, FairyTale.fid == FairyTaleLog.fid)
        .filter(FairyTale.uid == uid, FairyTaleLog.uid == uid)
        .filter(FairyTale.fid == fid, FairyTaleLog.fid == fid)
        .first())`

issue.title: Dataset analysis
issue.body:
1. Check the data quality (encoding, special characters etc)
2. Remove texts which are unsuitable for dependency analysis (business cards, menus, advertisements) 
3. A primitive analysis of the dataset: sentences each text, tokens each text, tokens each text. This should in certain degrees reflect the reliability of the dataset.

commits.message:
Adds locale middleware for URL handling

Introduces middleware to manage language locale in URLs,
defaulting to Hungarian if no locale is specified in the path.
Skips middleware for static assets and Next.js internals.

Improves user experience by ensuring consistent language
support across routing.

pull_request.body: Add a comprehensive TipTap-based contract editor to fulfill user requirements for contract drafting, templating, and export functionalities. This PR introduces a full-featured contract editor with a customizable header for formatting and export options, and a sidebar providing access to contract templates, predefined structures, and text suggestions, enhancing the user's ability to create and manage legal documents. ---

issue.title: Add Print & Export PDF feature for FoodDetail page
issue.body: ## 📌 Pull Request Summary - Added Print & Export as PDF functionality to the FoodDetail page. - Print: Uses react-to-print (v3 API) to open the browser print dialog with a clean recipe layout. - Export PDF: Uses html2pdf.js to download the food/recipe details as a styled PDF file. - Added print.css to hide non-essential UI (buttons, Add to Cart) and improve print/PDF layout. - Buttons styled to match the Add to Cart color theme. - Added a print/PDF header with app branding and export date. ## 🛠️ Type of Change Please select options that are relevant to your pull request - [ ] 🐛 Bug fix - [x] ✨ New feature - [ ] 🧹 Code refactor - [ ] 🧪 Tests added/updated - [ ] 📄 Documentation update - [ ] 🚀 Performance improvement - [ ] 🔧 Other (please describe): ## 🔗 Related Issue Closes #156 ## ✅ Checklist Please confirm the following before submitting: - [x] I have **tested** my changes locally - [x] I have run `npm run dev` or similar to check code style - [x] I have updated documentation (if necessary) - [x] My code follows the project’s coding conventions - [x] I have merged the latest `main` or `dev` branch - [x] I have performed a **self-review** of my own code. - [x] My changes **generate** no new warnings or errors. - [x] I have **commented** my code, especially in hard-to-understand areas - [x] I have **linked the related issue** ## 📸 Screenshots (if applicable) --- ## 🧠 Additional Notes 1) Tested on Chrome and Firefox; confirmed CORS-safe image loading in PDF. 2) Layout ensures no awkward page breaks for ingredients or steps. 3) Feature improves usability for offline users and those who prefer printed recipes.

issue.title: net/http: Request context is not canceled when `Server.WriteTimeout` is reached

labels.name: NeedsInvestigation
labels.description: Someone must examine and confirm this is a valid issue and not a duplicate of an existing one.

milestone.title: Unplanned
milestone.description: No plan to fix in any specific release.

issue.body:
### What version of Go are you using (`go version`)? 
$ go version
go version go1.19.5 linux/amd64
### Does this issue reproduce with the latest release? yes ### What operating system and processor architecture are you using (`go env`)?
go env Output
$ go env
GO111MODULE="on"
GOARCH="amd64"
GOBIN=""
GOCACHE="/home/patrik/.cache/go-build"
GOENV="/home/patrik/.config/go/env"
GOEXE=""
GOEXPERIMENT=""
GOFLAGS=""
GOHOSTARCH="amd64"
GOHOSTOS="linux"
GOINSECURE=""
GOMODCACHE="/home/patrik/go/pkg/mod"
GONOPROXY=""
GONOSUMDB=""
GOOS="linux"
GOPATH="/home/patrik/go"
GOPRIVATE=""
GOPROXY="https://proxy.golang.org,direct"
GOROOT="/usr/lib/go"
GOSUMDB="sum.golang.org"
GOTMPDIR=""
GOTOOLDIR="/usr/lib/go/pkg/tool/linux_amd64"
GOVCS=""
GOVERSION="go1.19.5"
GCCGO="gccgo"
GOAMD64="v1"
AR="ar"
CC="gcc"
CXX="g++"
CGO_ENABLED="1"
GOMOD="/home/patrik/git/oathkeeper/go.mod"
GOWORK=""
CGO_CFLAGS="-g -O2"
CGO_CPPFLAGS=""
CGO_CXXFLAGS="-g -O2"
CGO_FFLAGS="-g -O2"
CGO_LDFLAGS="-g -O2"
PKG_CONFIG="pkg-config"
GOGCCFLAGS="-fPIC -m64 -pthread -Wl,--no-gc-sections -fmessage-length=0 -fdebug-prefix-map=/tmp/go-build1543900704=/tmp/go-build -gno-record-gcc-switches"
### What did you do? ```go func TestWriteTimeoutCancellation(t *testing.T) { backend := httptest.NewUnstartedServer(http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) { r.Body.Close() // to show that it is not https://github.com/golang/go/issues/23262 time.Sleep(1 * time.Second) _, err := w.Write([]byte("ok")) ctxErr := r.Context().Err() _, _ = ctxErr, err // breakpoint here to see the errors, they are both nil })) backend.Config.WriteTimeout = 500 * time.Millisecond backend.EnableHTTP2 = true // you can also try false backend.Start() defer backend.Close() start := time.Now() res, err := backend.Client().Get(backend.URL) t.Logf("took %s", time.Since(start)) // for me this always takes 1s, although the write timeout is 500ms _, _ = res, err // breakpoint here, err is EOF, res is nil } ``` ### What did you expect to see? Client side: all requests are cancelled latest after the write timeout, why wait until the handler is done to not receive the result? Handler side: `r.Context()` is cancelled, so it can stop handling because the result is not returned anyway I have seen https://github.com/golang/go/issues/21389 which is kinda related, but not the same issue. I do understand that `w.Write()` does not immediately return an error because of buffering. I would expect the request context to be canceled immediately though. ### What did you see instead? Client: request took 1s, although the write timeout is 500ms Handler: no way to tell whether the timeout was triggered, potentially expensive or destructive work continues As is, I don't understand the use of `WriteTimeout` at all. It seems there is no effect, except for maybe big responses that might already be partially received by the client (see https://github.com/traefik/traefik/issues/9191#issuecomment-1197891601). I don't think this is a duplicate of #23262 because I see the behavior also when closing the body immediately. ### Workaround It seems pretty simple to just write a middleware that wraps the request context with a timeout: ```go func timeoutMiddleware(timeout time.Duration, next http.Handler) http.Handler { return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) { ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(r.Context(), timeout) defer cancel() r = r.WithContext(ctx) next.ServeHTTP(w, r) }) } ``` cc @alnr

comment.body:
+1 to this issue because I just burnt two hours trying to understand what was going wrong in my code 😢 

I initially misunderstood what `WriteTimeout` meant, I assumed it was the maximum time allowed for any call to write to the ResponseWriter, in order to protect against malicious/slow/disconnected clients. 

Even after understanding that it is fundamentally the total time for the request full lifecycle, I did not realise that my code was exceeding this timeout. The client was remaining connected long past `WriteTimeout` seconds, (twice as much in fact, I suspect Chrome was invisibly retrying), my call to `WriteHeader` on `http.ResponseWriter` was silently having no effect, and the request context was not being cancelled.
Even tracing through `WriteHeader` gave me no evidence that anything was wrong unfortunately.

A pragmatic solution that I would suggest is a bigger warning in the documentation, clarifying that setting this value won't cause the request context to be cancelled, and an explicit nudge towards `http.TimeoutHandler`

GL-5992-add-creator-achievements-table-to-creator-dashboar (#715)

* Refactor Creator Achievements API and Redux Integration

- Removed unused API endpoints and related logic for listing creator achievements, filtering by affiliate, period, and top performers, streamlining the codebase.
- Updated the creatorAchievementSlice to eliminate redundant loading states and error handling for removed API calls, enhancing performance and maintainability.
- Simplified the creator achievement controller and database functions by removing unnecessary methods, focusing on essential functionality.
- Adjusted routes to reflect the removal of deprecated endpoints, ensuring cleaner API structure and improved clarity in routing.
- Enhanced overall code readability and maintainability by cleaning up imports and unused variables across affected files.

* Add Creator Achievements Retrieval for Affiliates

- Implemented a new API endpoint to fetch creator achievements by affiliate ID, enhancing data accessibility for affiliate-specific achievements.
- Introduced the getMyCreatorAchievements function in the client API to facilitate retrieval of achievements based on affiliate ID, search parameters, and pagination.
- Updated the CreatorAchievementsPage to utilize the new CreatorAchievementsTable component, improving the display of achievements for affiliates.
- Removed the useCreatorAchievementsPage hook to streamline the component structure and enhance maintainability.
- Enhanced the CreatorDashboardTab to include the CreatorAchievementsTable, providing a comprehensive view of achievements within the profile page.

* Refactor Creator Achievements Page and Table Integration

- Streamlined the CreatorAchievementsPage by removing direct modal imports and integrating modal components within the CreatorAchievementsTable.
- Enhanced the useCreatorAchievementsTable hook to include title actions for creating achievements and running bulk payouts, improving user interaction.
- Updated the CreatorAchievementsTable component to accept titleActions as a prop, ensuring a more cohesive structure and better maintainability.
- Cleaned up unused imports and optimized component structure for improved readability.

* Refactor Creator Achievements Logic and API Error Handling

- Removed the useEffect hook in useCreatorAchievementsTable to streamline data fetching based on affiliate ID.
- Added console logging for achievements and errors in the creator achievement controller to enhance debugging capabilities.
- Updated the creator achievement services to ensure affiliate filtering only occurs when an affiliate ID is provided, improving data retrieval accuracy.

* Enhance Creator Achievements Table with Admin Controls

- Added conditional rendering for edit and delete buttons in the CreatorAchievementsTable, allowing only admin users to access these actions.
- Integrated current user state to determine admin status, improving security and user experience.
- Updated dependencies in the useEffect hook to include current_user.isAdmin for better performance and reactivity.

* Update Creator Achievements Table and View Modal

- Changed default sorting index for the creatorAchievementTable from 9 to 0 for improved data display.
- Enhanced the CreatorAchievementsTable by adding new columns for "Payment Status" and "Created" date, improving the visibility of key achievement metrics.
- Refactored the ViewAchievementModal to include additional performance metrics and improved styling for better user experience.
- Updated the layout of the modal to enhance readability and organization of achievement details, including task completions and promo code information.
- Cleaned up unused imports and optimized component structure for better maintainability.

* Refactor CreatorDashboardTab to Simplify Props and Update Table Structure

- Removed monthlyEarnings prop from CreatorDashboardTab for cleaner component structure.
- Reorganized the layout to include CreatorAchievementsTable and PaychecksTable, enhancing the display of creator metrics.
- Updated comments to reflect the new table content, improving code clarity and maintainability.

* Refactor CreatorAchievementsTable and Dashboard Integration

- Updated CreatorAchievementsTable to accept noURLParams prop for improved flexibility in URL handling.
- Enhanced useCreatorAchievementsTable to conditionally render title actions based on admin status, improving user experience for non-admin users.
- Cleaned up imports and optimized component structure for better maintainability.

Set up the basic Go project structure with CLI framework for the Gohan static site generator.

## Tasks
- [ ] Initialize Go module with proper project structure

- [ ] `go mod init` completed with proper module name

fix: Implement robust script loading for installer

This commit fixes a critical bug where the installation wizard would either show a blank page or get stuck on the "Loading..." message. This was caused by a race condition with the JavaScript rendering logic.

The fix implements a more robust method for initializing the React application:
- The main installer script now exposes a global `init` function.
- An inline script is added via `wp_add_inline_script` to call this `init` function after the DOM is ready.
- A guard clause was added to check for the `wp.element` dependency before execution.

This ensures the script runs at the correct time, resolving the rendering issue.
